<subSubSection id="C19FD790C653FAF9AC58C9E9C1D528F8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F65FE21DC1EF9A1CA0BEF0363B22ECF3" pageNumber="2">Introduction</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E298ADB70810EC03F98FF3E6F1D2268" lastPageNumber="3" pageNumber="2">
Myers (1933) established the genus 
<taxonomicName id="D90AEFAF22F630D7D6401A0088654C11" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F37E2B4C-B726-4D09-B675-CB3E4082BD81" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypanchax Myers 1933:1" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypanchax</taxonomicName>
for 
<taxonomicName id="9F860104A931F474DED47EE908C93DF5" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2CE2F105-250A-4F28-A0DC-17203140248D" authority="Agassiz, 1846" authorityName="Agassiz" authorityYear="1846" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Haplochilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Haplochilus playfairii Günther 1866:314" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="playfairii">
Haplochilus playfairii 
<normalizedToken id="2DE498305F45694DF6014186072F6361" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
, 1866
</taxonomicName>
, a robust killifish endemic to the granitic Seychelles (Playfair and 
<normalizedToken id="F2B52CBC4E40E367188F1BA1ED7CAE82" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
, 1866). He included two Malagasy species, 
<taxonomicName id="B9ABA98C4972DDE1A1B8F6BBBF7BE29F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:00C4F603-3BD2-4750-A796-A61E9FA053B6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Poecilia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Poecilia omalonota Duméril 1861:257" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omalonota">
Poecilia omalonota 
<normalizedToken id="8BA822F2313B68E2C33B0EEE33D02A01" originalValue="Duméril">Dumeril</normalizedToken>
, 1861
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FD1A6E9DC45D33B07038D03127EC2874" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B1B4C5F9-0636-4EAD-8741-A4FE89B51E97" authority="Valenciennes, 1846" authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1846" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Panchax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Panchax sakaramyi Holly 1928:313" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sakaramyi">Panchax sakaramyi Holly, 1928</taxonomicName>
in his new genus. This attribution appears to have been made on biogeographic grounds, as Myers clearly indicated that he had not examined specimens of either Malagasy species. Scheel (1968) refined Myer’s definition of the genus with the addition of two additional diagnostic characters. However, the material of 
<taxonomicName id="0398DE75A8D183E4F3CDCF053803FB73" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:00C4F603-3BD2-4750-A796-A61E9FA053B6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Poeciliidae" genus="Poecilia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Poecilia omalonota Duméril 1861:257" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omalonota">P. omalonota</taxonomicName>
available to Scheel consisted of aquarium-reared specimens descended from fish collected from the lower reaches of the westward-flowing Betsiboka River, on the mainland of Madagascar (Arnoult, 1955), whereas the type material of 
<taxonomicName id="ABBD9F4F9521AACAAC7D7D7B8409D8F6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omalonotus">P. omalonotus</taxonomicName>
actually came from the island of Nosy Be, off northwestern Madagascar. Subsequent collecting has demonstrated these two taxa differ sufficiently in coloration and morphology to warrant recognition as separate species. Parenti (1981) subsequently redefined the genus, placing particular emphasis upon several skeletal apomorphies. However, Parenti neither examined topotypical material of 
<taxonomicName id="48567C95C345C9E1A54F7DAEEAAE3DE6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omalonotus">P. omalonotus</taxonomicName>
nor specimens of the other two nominal Malagasy species, 
<taxonomicName id="F3BF09C11605F77B05C1B28F4368DD30" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sakaramyi">P. sakaramyi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7C9C72C799E0148A917170256074C07F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="2" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nuchimaculatus">P. nuchimaculatus (Guichenot, 1866)</taxonomicName>
. Her inclusion of the Malagasy species within the genus was thus tentative.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="16BF74634A73E488B0906C27E1E64B9D" pageNumber="3">
Fieldwork in Madagascar undertaken since 1993 has resulted in the collection of larger series of both 
<taxonomicName id="69623D454566388ABA1B4FFE22B51373" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omalonotus">P. omalonotus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D39F3921D3E13E7378D40D27C8D2B9AF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sakaramyi">P. sakaramyi</taxonomicName>
, and in the discovery of additional aplocheilid taxa that cannot be referred to previously published nomina. In light of these discoveries, it is appropriate to reexamine Parenti’s definition of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="002C06AFF381454B24015502C13F3E10" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F37E2B4C-B726-4D09-B675-CB3E4082BD81" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pachypanchax Myers 1933:1" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pachypanchax</taxonomicName>
, redescribe 
<taxonomicName id="215B197C47CD87BE44EDD4FAB1267650" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omalonotus">P. omalonotus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6E5FC8B19D39CDB74232181725009DBC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Aplocheilidae" genus="Pachypanchax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sakaramyi">P. sakaramyi</taxonomicName>
, and describe four of these new taxa. Three more recently discovered Malagasy species remain to be described.
</paragraph>
